cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a mechanism for associating UML models with definitions, which is a software engineering concern. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the syntax and semantics of UML, which can be seen as a language. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper proposes an axiomatic style of semantics for UML family members. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as UML is often used in the design of AI systems. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a way to organize and share large amounts of information (i.e. prefaces) related to UML family members.
